      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in a condition that defies its vintage. This specimen features the legendary S54B32 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, delivering 333 hp with razor-sharp response via six individual throttle bodies. The high-pressure double-VANOS system has been meticulously serviced to ensure optimal cam timing across the rev range. Power is managed through a precise Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and delivered to the rear wheels via the variable M differential lock. The chassis remains impeccably rigid, with a verified subframe inspection confirming zero fatigue or stress fractures. Finished in Carbon Black over Nappa leather, the exterior retains its original factory luster with no clear coat degradation. Mechanically stock and cosmetically flawless, this is a true driver\u2019s car for the discerning collector.",
